title: Grateful Dead Live at The Spectrum on 1983-04-26
description:
Set 1

Shakedown Street-> Minglewood Blues, They Love Each Other, Me and My Uncle, Mexicali Blues, Maybe You Know How I Feel, West LA Fadeaway, My Brother Esau, It Must Have Been the Roses, Let It Grow

Set 2

Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower, Women Are Smarter-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Nobody's Fault But Mine-> Morning Dew-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: U.S. Blues

correct info from www.setlists.net

reviews.review_text:
Philly Phillies Start Lookin Good One of the great shows.  A smoker from the get-go.   Very cool to have this lineage source.  

Thank-you

Thanks, just found these Thanks Vernon, I just found these Healy tapes after looking for other copies of the 4-5-91. I wouldn't care if it was 50 years later, getting a copy of a Healy tape is an awesome day.
Thanks'
AZ

Superb playback! One of the crispest sounding recording i have ever heard, extremely well done!  Thank you so much for sharing, this is why i donate to archive.org, amazing organization with collaboration from some of the most unique people on the planet!
